Amplitude is a comprehensive behavioral analytics platform that enables organizations to understand user behavior through event tracking, experimentation, and data analysis. The platform consists of multiple interconnected products designed to capture, analyze, and act on user interaction data across web, mobile, and server-side applications.

## Core Product Architecture

The platform is built around several primary product areas that work together to provide end-to-end analytics capabilities:

**Analytics** serves as the core behavioral analysis engine, featuring multiple chart types including Event Segmentation, Funnel Analysis, Retention Analysis, User Sessions, Journeys, Personas, Lifecycle, Stickiness, Compass, Impact Analysis, Engagement Matrix, Revenue LTV, Data Tables, and Experiment Results. These charts enable deep analysis of user behavior patterns, conversion flows, and business metrics.

**Amplitude Experiment** provides feature flagging and A/B testing capabilities, encompassing experiment design, statistical analysis, advanced techniques, and comprehensive result interpretation. The platform includes experiment theory documentation, workflow management, troubleshooting guides, and "under the hood" technical details.

**Data Management (CDP)** handles data ingestion, transformation, and distribution through source catalogs, destination catalogs, audiences, warehouse-native capabilities, and PII integrations. This creates a unified customer data platform for managing user information across systems.

**Session Replay** captures and analyzes user session recordings to provide qualitative insights into user behavior and experience issues.

**Guides and Surveys** enables in-product messaging and user feedback collection to drive engagement and gather user insights.

